<!-- FAQ -->
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq supporting-questions">
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How does a sensory bed sheet compare to a weighted blanket?</h3><p>Both provide deep pressure stimulation, but sensory sheets do it through compression (stretchy fabric pulling around you) rather than weight. The key advantage is breathability — no heat buildup. The tradeoff is you can't easily kick it off like a blanket.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>What size mattress does the 38"x60" fit?</h3><p>This fits a twin mattress or serves as a body-sized compression zone on a larger bed. It's designed more for individual use than covering a queen or king bed.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can adults use this or is it just for kids?</h3><p>Absolutely for adults. While it's marketed for children with sensory needs, adults who enjoy weighted blankets, have anxiety, or simply like tight compression will benefit equally.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How do I wash it?</h3><p>Machine wash cold on gentle cycle, tumble dry low. The polyester material holds up well but avoid high heat to preserve the elastic stretch.</p></div>
</div>

